N: \mathbb Z[\sqrt{3}] \to \mathbb Z, \qquad N(x+\sqrt{3} y) = x^2 - 3y^2
(a+\sqrt{3}b)^{-1}=x+\sqrt 3 y
1 = N(1) = N((a+\sqrt{3}b)(x + \sqrt{3}y)) = (a^2 - 3b^2)(x^2 - 3y^2)
\pm 1 = (a^2 - 3b^2) = (a+\sqrt{3}b)(a-\sqrt{3}b)
a,b
a^2 - 3b^2 = \pm 1
a = \sqrt{3b^2 \pm 1}
